commit.title: Documenting syntax "injection ... as [= pat1 ... patn ]".
commit.message:
Documenting syntax "injection ... as [= pat1 ... patn ]".

To prevent confusion, forbidding a mix of the "injection term as pat1
... patn" and of the "injection term as [= pat1 ... patn]" syntax: If
a "[= ...]" occurs, this should be a singleton list of patterns.

Modifying theories to preferably use the "[= ]" syntax, and,
sometimes, to use "intros [= ...]" rather than things like
"intros H; injection H as [= ...]".

commit.message:
Documenting syntax "injection ... as [= pat1 ... patn ]".

To prevent confusion, forbidding a mix of the "injection term as pat1
... patn" and of the "injection term as [= pat1 ... patn]" syntax: If
a "[= ...]" occurs, this should be a singleton list of patterns.

Modifying theories to preferably use the "[= ]" syntax, and,
sometimes, to use "intros [= ...]" rather than things like
"intros H; injection H as [= ...]".
